title: SONNY ROLLINS & CO. 1964 / RCA / Jim Hall, Herbie Hancock
description:
Just in case you don't want the entire 6 CD set (complete Rollins on RCA)

here is a very choice part of it.



.....Rollins had fought hard for his integrity, and has never been known

to capitulate to record company dictates.  The music that he recorded

in 1964 was therefore indicative of his own needs and desires at the time, 

and effectively announced the creative format upon which he would 

ultimately settle.............Bob Blumenthal (from included booklet)




13 tracks from 6 trio and quartet sessions including some previously

unreleased
